\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {subsection}{\numberline {7.3}PLUM Verification With and Without the Precompile}{61}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{ssec:headline}{{7.3}{61}{}{subsection.7.3}{}}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces PLUM single-signature verification, prove mode, $\lambda =80$, M5~Pro 24~GB. We refer to the three SP1 arms as \emph  {Cell~1} (no precompile), \emph  {Cell~2} (Griffin-$\mathbb  {F}_p^{192}$ precompile), and \emph  {Cell~3} (software SHA-3 control) throughout. The precompile-free baseline does not complete; the precompile arm completes in $32.53$~min. The SHA-3 arm is a \emph  {control} (PLUM with a standard hash computed in software, no hash precompile, only the shared \texttt  {UINT256\_MUL} field-arithmetic precompile active), not a deployable PLUM variant. These are the May calibrated-reference runs; a $2026$-06-13 current-build re-measurement gives Cell~2 $17.81$~min and Cell~3 $16.15$~min ($n=2$ per arm, same session), confirming feasibility and the inversion sign, the difference attributed to build drift (\S  \ref {ssec:headline}). $^\ddag  $RISC~Zero receipt-verify wall-clock not separately logged; the receipt verified.}}{61}{}\protected@file@percent }
