\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Aurora over a single Loquat-verification R1CS, M5~Pro 24~GB; mean of three solo runs with the per-run range in parentheses (run records in \texttt  {docs/measurements/pub\_hardening\_20260610}). This is the \emph  {Loquat}-instantiated circuit over $\mathbb  {F}_{p^2}$ ($127$-bit base)~\cite  {10.1007/978-981-96-0957-4_3} at single-verification scope; the full BDEC relation is two such verifications ($\approx $twice this), not run statically. Prover time includes Aurora parameter setup but is not a recompile-time measurement (\S  \ref {ssec:churn-eval}). Achieved security $107.5$ bits, below the $128$ target. Verification \texttt  {ACCEPT} in every run.}}{63}{}\protected@file@percent }
