\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Same-scheme substrate comparison: one Loquat verification, $\lambda =80$, M5~Pro 24~GB, three solo runs per leg, neither zero-knowledge. The Aurora leg is the mean of Table~\ref {tab:aurora-ref}; the SP1 leg is the range of three runs ($44.4$, $47.4$, $64.0$~min) under the documented reduced-memory configuration (\S  \ref {ssec:settings-justify}), succinct core STARK, peak RSS $14.1$--$15.4$~GiB, execute-mode cost $397{,}227{,}544$ cycles (run records in \texttt  {docs/measurements/pub\_hardening\_20260610}). Only the substrate differs (native R1CS versus zkVM emulation); the $12$--$17\times $ prover-time gap is the cost of the zkVM substrate for this scheme. This isolates the substrate for \emph  {Loquat}; it does not transfer to PLUM, which has no $127$-bit Aurora harness.}}{64}{}\protected@file@percent }
